first quarter of this year achieve a higher profit as a result of forex rate gains from the fall of the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  The state firm gained additional income from forex gains by 603% at Rp14.3 billion compared to Rp2 billion in the first three months of last year. \par \par \uc2  An analyst at a foreign securities company has said that Indosat's higher profit of 33% to Rp176 billion in the first three months of this year was due to income from interest. \par \par \uc2  "Indosat has net cash position," said the analyst. \par \par \uc2  Although technically the income ought not be factored into its main revenue, Indosat is sounder than other companies. \par \par \uc2  Adrian is optimistic that Indosat would reach its target and maintain its level of profitability in the next three quarters. \par \par \uc2  "Our optimism is based on its amazing international call traffic volume which continues to grow," he said. \par \par \uc2  The volume of incoming and outgoing international calls has grown by an average of 18% compared to 17.9% the year before. \par \par \uc2  "The figure is much higher than our projected figure of 5.7% as we had thought that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis would have an effect on international calls," said Adrian. \par \par \uc2  In the first quarter of 1998 Indosat also increased its \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  for problematic bills to Rp7.2 billion from Rp1.7 billion, causing its general and administrative costs to rise by 56.7%. \par \par \uc2  Raising the \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  is a conservative move by Indosat in the face of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation and is aimed at dealing with income from cellular phone operations. \par \par \uc2  On its diversification plan, Safwan Natanagara, director of Indosat, said that the company would continue to support and boost the synergy of its subsidiaries. \par \par \uc2  He said that in the short term income from investment in its diversified businesses would not be as high as projected because of the current situation. "But we are convinced that our long-term projection, especially the contribution of 20% to the company by the year 2005, will not change," said Safwan. \par \par \uc2  In relation to its 1998 investment plan, Safwan said that the state company is set to allocate between Rp450 billion and Rp500 billion. (amu). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du5i0017b\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Property shares remain weak. \b0\par\par\uc2 252 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 May 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Trading of property shares last week remained slow in line with the bourse's poor showing. \par \par \uc2  The property sector's prospects still looked dim, causing trading of its shares to be dominated by action selling. \par \par \uc2  Of the 25 property shares, 20 saw themselves corrected which resulted in the sector's index to end at 36.031 last week. \par \par \uc2  This means that the sector was corrected 18.36% last week, falling from the level of 44.135. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, 69.7 million shares worth Rp59.3 billion changed hands. \par \par \uc2  As the prices are now below their nominal value, property shares are actually very cheap. \par \par \uc2  High \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  as a result of issuers' swelling debts are taking its toll on its current year performance. \par \par \uc2  Amidst \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  caused by riots, the property sector is sure to plummet even lower. All the more so as many buildings that were about to be bought or leased by foreign investors, were destroyed by riots. \par \par \uc2  Under such a dire situation, it is likely that property shares would remain under selling pressure this week as potential investors tend to wait for further developments. \par \par \uc2  Last week saw Lippo Cikarang shares being most actively traded, with 17.98 million units worth Rp12.60 billion changing hands. \par \par \uc2  Putra Surya Perkasa Tbk booked the largest drop at 44.44%, from Rp225 to Rp126 per unit. \par \par \uc2  Shares of three property firms of the Lippo Group also saw their value drop. \par \par \uc2  3/4 Sigma Research Institute. \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du5j0017l\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
