\par\par \b \uc2  Macroeconomic targets need revising - Neiss. \b0\par\par\uc2 464 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 May 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  9 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Macroeconomic assumptions of the International Monetary Fund's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform program for Indonesia will have to be adjusted due to the country's worsening situation, IMF Asia Pacific director Hubert Neiss admitted yesterday. \par \par \uc2  "Yes, we have to make adaptations in the macroeconomic framework to the new situation that unfortunately is even weaker than before," he told media following a 45-minute meeting with President B.J. Habibie. \par \par \uc2  Neiss arrived in Jakarta Tuesday for a marathon round of talks with several ministers, opposition leaders and foreign ambassadors until Saturday. \par \par \uc2  He is reviewing the country's situation following the recent bloody unrest, and his report will be the basis for the IMF's board of directors to decide on the disbursement of another US$1 billion in bailout funds. \par \par \uc2  Neiss said falling production, skyrocketing inflation and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the rupiah exchange rate had caused a further decline since his last visit. \par \par \uc2  He declined comment on whether the rupiah year-end exchange rate target of Rp 6,000 to the dollar was still realistic. \par \par \uc2  "We don't know at this point what is the good forecast for the exchange rate," he said. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah is currently hovering at about Rp 10,500 against the U.S. dollar, from Rp 2,450 in July last year when the crisis began to unfold. \par \par \uc2  Neiss stressed there was no need to revise the structural reform program. \par \par \uc2  "The very detailed and far reaching structural reforms will stay as it was originally agreed." \par \par \uc2  He added that financial reform was the centerpiece of the IMF reform program and had become an urgent necessity. \par \par \uc2  "There will be no need for revision, but there is a need for strengthening and possibly acceleration in the rehabilitation of the financial sector." \par \par \uc2  He explained that it would take time for the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to recover, with much depending on a return in investor confidence and political stability. \par \par \uc2  "Eventually, what is needed is a return of capital, not only foreign capital but that which belongs to Indonesians." \par \par \uc2  Neiss said another important topic to discuss with the new government was monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "That is very important because we have had serious increasing inflation which is very important to stop. We have to restrain monetary expansion." \par \par \uc2  He said he would discuss the best possible ways to solve the problem with \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The two important areas to cover are the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ." \par \par \uc2  He added that the discussion would also cover the country's overseas private sector debt. \par \par \uc2  "We can expect some first concrete results will emerge," he said. He added that the proposed Mexican model for resolving the debt conundrum offered several attractions to creditors and simultaneously limited the financial load of the government. (rei/prb) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du5t002zp\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
