\par\par \b \uc2  Rice procurement may hit 20-year low. \b0\par\par\uc2 640 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 June 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The State Logistics Agency (Bulog) estimated yesterday that its domestic rice procurement may fall to 250,000 metric tons this year, the lowest level in 20 years, due to a decline in rice production. \par \par \uc2  Bulog chairman Beddu Amang, however, said that the agency would be able to meet the domestic demand with imports estimated to reach three million tons this year. \par \par \uc2  He said Bulog would import 3.1 million tons of rice if its procurement reached only 250,000 tons. "But if the agency could purchase 500,000 tons from local farmers, imports would be cut to around 2.85 million tons," he told reporters after a hearing with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ' Commission III for agriculture, forestry and plantations, transmigration and food affairs. \par \par \uc2  Bulog said its rice procurement in the January-to-May period plunged 94 percent to 96,512 tons from 1.55 million tons in the same period last year. \par \par \uc2  "This year's procurement will likely reach only 250,000 tons. It is the lowest level in 20 years," Beddu said, adding that domestic procurement reached 1.95 million tons last year and 1.43 million tons in 1996. \par \par \uc2  He said Bulog initially planned to buy about one million tons locally this year but the decline in production caused by the drought made it impossible to meet the procurement target. \par \par \uc2  Bulog's rice stocks on May 28 stood at 2.5 million tons, sugar at 592,686 tons, wheat flour at 325,000 tons and soybeans at 102,596 tons. \par \par \uc2  He said the rice stocks were sufficient for three months while those for sugar and other commodities could last up to 28 months. \par \par \uc2  Beddu, however, ruled out a possible rice shortage in the coming months. \par \par \uc2  "Don't worry, our stocks will increase because our rice imports continue to flow in from Thailand, China and Vietnam and we are still receiving rice aid from other countries." \par \par \uc2  He added that Japan has pledged to supply 500,000 tons of rice in soft loans with a 30-year maturity and 100,000 tons as a grant, Taiwan would sell 200,000 tons, China 250,000 tons and Vietnam 10,000 tons and Thailand would give 5,000 tons in a grant. \par \par \uc2  The government is still negotiating for another 400,000-ton rice grant from Japan and 100,000 tons from Taiwan, Beddu said. \par \par \uc2  Recent reports have said Thai rice and sugar exporters have stopped accepting Indonesia's letters of credit (L/Cs) for rice and sugar orders due to the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions here. \par \par \uc2  But Beddu said that Thai exporters had agreed to take Indonesia's L/Cs if they were opened by state banks and endorsed by foreign banks in Singapore. \par \par \uc2  Beddu also said yesterday that Bulog planned to invite local and international tenders to buy commodities for the agency. \par \par \uc2  "We will no longer go to the international market quietly. We will invite foreign suppliers through international tenders if necessary. This will apply to any commodities," Beddu said. \par \par \uc2  Beddu added that the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  on basic commodities would remain until the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation improved to help remedy the pains of the common people. \par \par \uc2  "The International Monetary Fund has agreed on the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  which will amount to Rp 5.3 trillion (US$460 million) to import basic commodities. The IMF has asked us to gradually remove the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  but this depends on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions," he said. \par \par \uc2  The government's agreement with the IMF stipulates that \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  on all commodities, except rice, must be abolished by Oct. 1. \par \par \uc2  "But if we are not able to scrap the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , then we don't have to. We understand that the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  will burden our state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but on the other hand we have to help our people," Beddu said. (gis) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du63003ad\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Manufacturing index fell 15.98% in May. \b0\par\par\uc2 299 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 June 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA: Trade of manufacturing stocks was thin during last month, with investors coming under selling pressure. Manufacturing index lost 15.98% to 65.45 by May 29. \par \par \uc2  The fall of manufacturing stocks was due to the across-the-board weakening of the Jakarta Stock Exchange. Composite index fell 8.62% to 420.465. The weaker rupiah value against the US dollar has also affected the stocks. \par \par \uc2  The monetary authorities' \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of raising the interest rate of the 58% level has further choked the business community. That has placed manufacturing companies into a deeper trouble to fund production activities. \par \par \uc2  Further, a wave of student demonstrations in the parliamentary compound has also dampened sentiment to invest in the bourse. Investors opted to cut losses on manufacturing stock at that time. Investors were of view that such demonstrations would affect political stability badly. \par \par \uc2  The demonstrations had been followed by mass unrests, including arsoning and looting of a number of supermarkets and department stores on May 13 and 14. The unrests had practically paralyzed distribution of necessities to many people. Foreign investors also fled the country and many have been reluctant to return. \par \par \uc2  In short, the political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  reigns and affects the investment climate, especially that in the capital market. \par \par \uc2  Soeharto's resignation from presidency gave only temporary effect. The Jakarta stock exchange dimmed again as the political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition seems to change almost on daily basis. \par \par \uc2  Overall, share transactions were thin last month. Sectoral shares that changed hands totaled 534.643 million, worth Rp 560.858 billion. \par \par \uc2  Trade in the coming few weeks are also bound to overwhelmed by \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability is the key to the recovery of investment climate in the bourse. \par \par \uc2  Sigma Research Institute, Inc. \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du63001ca\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
