\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Economy \highlight\uc2  may not last 3 months - Econit. \b0\par\par\uc2 823 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 June 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  may not survive for more than three months unless the country elects a new credible government, according to an independent think tank. \par \par \uc2  Plunging foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the ballooning \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the severe lack of capital inflow are all serious threats to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 's ability to survive the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, the Econit Advisory Group said yesterday in a discussion. \par \par \uc2  "We must have a government which is credible both domestically and internationally," said the group's senior economist Rizal Ramli. \par \par \uc2  He explained that President B.J. Habibie, and his \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministerial team were not a solution but still part of the problem because they had served during the Soeharto era. \par \par \uc2  "It is therefore difficult to expect them to change their conventional ways of thinking in dealing with the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis," Rizal noted. \par \par \uc2  Former president Soeharto ended his 32-year rule last month after pressure from the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , students and most mass organizations. He handed over the reins of power to his protege Habibie, at the time the vice president. \par \par \uc2  However, Habibie himself is still facing strong pressure to quickly arrange a general election based on a new political system to elect a credible leader who is trusted by the people. \par \par \uc2  Econit dubbed the current government as "a new brand of old stock." \par \par \uc2  Rizal explained that because the solution to the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis depended largely on a solution to the political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , a credible government must be elected quickly. \par \par \uc2  "Time is running against us because of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  paralysis," said Arif Arryman, another Econit economist. \par \par \uc2  Habibie, who has promised a general election sometime next year and presidential elections before the end of next year, seems to have started gaining international confidence. \par \par \uc2  The World Bank said yesterday that it had resumed a US$225 million loan to reduce poverty in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  IMF Asia-Pacific Director Hubert Neiss has also said that Habibie had shown positive steps toward the implementation of human rights, and that the country had an impressive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team led by Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita. \par \par \uc2  The IMF is expected to soon disburse another $1 billion in bailout money to Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia is currently being administered to by the IMF through its multibillion dollar sweeping \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs designed to lift the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  from its worst crisis in three decades. \par \par \uc2  Econit, however, said that unless the country had a legitimate and credible government the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would soon collapse. \par \par \uc2  It cited several indicators. \par \par \uc2  Despite the punitively high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the rupiah has failed to stabilize against the U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  The local currency plunged to its lowest level of Rp 17,000 to the dollar in January, against Rp 2,450 in July before the crisis. The currency was hovering at around Rp 12,000 yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Rizal said the sharp depreciation of the rupiah had failed to boost exports as businesses had been hurt by the high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the international community's refusal to accept letters of credit from most Indonesian banks. \par \par \uc2  "This is a very sad situation because exports are the best and most effective way out of the crisis," he said. \par \par \uc2  He also said that the country's alarmingly low level of foreign \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 , of only around $14.5 billion compared to the short-term overseas debt obligation of $14.2 billion and import needs of $4 billion per month, was exacerbated by the virtual halt of capital inflow. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  hardships are being worsened by the high inflation rate which Econit estimates will reach more than 80 percent this year due to the severe shortage of essential food items. \par \par \uc2  Econit expects the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to contract 10 percent this year against an average growth rate of 7 percent before the crisis. \par \par \uc2  "This would cause additional unemployment of around 20 million," Rizal said \par \par \uc2  Arif said that even with the rupiah standing at Rp 8,000, the government would not be able to finance its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He pointed out that with that exchange rate and the price of oil at $14 per barrel, government revenue would only be Rp 114 trillion compared to \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Rp 125 trillion, excluding \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  on essential foods. \par \par \uc2  "Actually, with an exchange rate of above Rp 6,000, we're already bankrupt," he said, adding that the government may soon run out of money even to pay its personnel and the military. \par \par \uc2  Given the limited foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  and exploding \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government's blanket guarantee on the claims on banks, massive liquidity injection to problem banks and \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  on staple goods and medicines are only hastening the government's descent into bankruptcy, Arif explained. \par \par \uc2  "The personal credibility of the country's leader is key to the recovery," Rizal said, pointing out that other crisis-hit countries, Thailand and South Korea, were able to recover because of their new, credible, governments. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du64003bz\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
