\par\par \b \uc2  BNI expects nonperforming loans to expand. \b0\par\par\uc2 574 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 June 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  7 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Publicly listed Bank Negara Indonesia (BNI) plans to boost its loan loss \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  to offset a sharp rise in nonperforming loans due to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, a top official has said. \par \par \uc2  "More earnings need to be retained to increase the loan loss \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  because we anticipate nonperforming loans to rise in 1998," BNI president Widigdo Sukarman told reporters yesterday following the bank's annual shareholders meeting. \par \par \uc2  He declined, however, to disclose the increase, but said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis would force all banks to face the same problem because the real sector had been badly hit by difficulties in obtaining imported raw materials and suffered from high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  BNI reported its outstanding loans totaled Rp 60.28 trillion (US$4.67 billion) as of March, a jump of more than 155 percent against the level of the same period last year. \par \par \uc2  Widigdo said the sharp rise was due to the plunging value of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar which caused its foreign exchange lendings to soar in local currency terms. \par \par \uc2  He also said the shareholders had agreed to the bank's proposal to provide an annual dividend of only 20 percent of net earnings to increase the loan loss \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The dividend for 1997 was fixed at Rp 14 per share. \par \par \uc2  BNI reported 1997 net earnings declined 5.49 percent to Rp 315.24 billion from Rp 335.13 billion in 1996. \par \par \uc2  The bank attributed the weaker performance to the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis and the 336.93 percent increase in loan loss provisions to Rp 689.72 billion during the year from Rp 157.85 billion in 1996. \par \par \uc2  The bank's net profit in the first quarter of 1998 totaled Rp 36 billion, Widigdo said, but he did not provide comparative figures. \par \par \uc2  Total deposits during the first quarter jumped more than 111 percent to Rp 42.41 trillion against the same period in 1997, or a 44.73 percent increase compared to the deposit position as of the end of December. \par \par \uc2  The bank attributed the sharp increase to high time-deposit \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  BNI also reported that total assets in the first quarter of this year soared more than 126 percent to Rp 81.24 trillion from the same period in 1997, or a 42 percent increase from the full year's level. \par \par \uc2  Domestic banks have aggressively pushed up \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to retain depositors' money due to rising \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the industry following the closing down of 16 banks in November. \par \par \uc2  Widigdo, however, stressed that \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  must gradually come down but that it would not significantly lessen the effectiveness of the government's macroeconomic \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  BNI and other banks have started to lower their \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \b \highlight22\uc2 Interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  for one-month time deposits have dropped from 60 percent last month to 55 percent last week, while settling at 48 percent yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Widigdo said the government's high interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  aiming to contain inflation and stabilize the rupiah was no longer effective. \par \par \uc2  Shareholders also agreed yester