\par\par \b \uc2  Rupiah breaks 13,000 barrier against dollar. \b0\par\par\uc2 582 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 June 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The rupiah broke the 13,000 barrier against the U.S. dollar in thin morning trade yesterday but managed to recover slightly in the afternoon to end the day at 12,900. \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers attributed the rupiah's slump to political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  at home and weak regional markets. \par \par \uc2  The sharp drop in the currency dragged down local stock prices as investors became concerned that the rupiah's fall would further dampen operations of publicly listed companies. \par \par \uc2  The market sentiment, hit by political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the last several weeks, was affected by fears over the Japanese yen's drop against the U.S. dollar and a possible devaluation of the Chinese yuan. \par \par \uc2  "This negative sentiment hit both the rupiah and the stock market," one analyst said. \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers said that the rupiah, which opened yesterday at 11,800 against the greenback, might further sink to 15,000 in the days ahead should regional markets continue their downward trend on top of political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  at home. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah plunged to 14,500 against the dollar on Jan. 27 after reaching a record low of 16,800 on Jan. 9. \par \par \uc2  "Should there be any major social and political unrest in the days ahead, the rupiah could touch uncharted territory," one dealer said. \par \par \uc2  The country's social and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  have remained unresolved, with more protests seen in several major cities here demanding companies to raise wages and an end to rampant nepotism and corruption. \par \par \uc2  Following a \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  protest against Maspion Group in Surabaya, East Java, the previous day, more than 1,000 employees of the state-owned airline PT Garuda Indonesia, including pilots in their airline uniforms, staged a protest demanding a total management overhaul and the eradication of corruption, nepotism and collusion from the airline. \par \par \uc2  An economist with Danareksa Sekuritas, Raden Pardede, said yesterday that similar protests would further hamper the country's efforts to improve its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation. \par \par \uc2  "If similar social unrest takes place, the country's political situation will worsen," he said, adding that efforts to bring the country out of its dire crisis would not bear any fruit. \par \par \uc2  He said the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and financial markets would likely weaken in the medium and long terms if there were no clear-cut measures introduced by the government to address political problems. \par \par \uc2  "Political stability is the key factor in healing the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and financial markets. The longer the political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  remain unresolved, the longer it will take to improve our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," another analyst said. \par \par \uc2  Following the fall of the rupiah, stock prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) closed 0.7 percent lower or 2.92 points to 408.08 yesterday on a total turnover of 250.72 million shares on the regular market valued at Rp 235.59 billion (US$20.48 million). \par \par \uc2  Stockbrokers said that trading in the local bourse remained lethargic for the whole trading day with most investors seen placing large selling orders on most stocks. \par \par \uc2  "I think investors are fully aware that the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will continue to deteriorate," a dealer with Bali Securities said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  He attributed the mild decline in the main price to arbitrage buying on cross-listed stocks like PT Telkom and Indosat to benefit from the weakening rupiah. \par \par \uc2  The stock prices of the state telecommunications firm PT Telkom and satellite operator Indosat account for about 30 percent of market capitalization in the local exchange. (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du6b006js\par }\page {\par\fs20\b  \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty \highlight\uc2  shrouds Jakarta bourse. \b0\par\par\uc2 386 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 June 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 -shrouded Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  continues to affect investors' verve to speculate in the stock market. Already investors are baffled by high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , skyrocketing inflation and a prediction that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will shrink by 10 percent. \par \par \uc2  The good news that Indonesia has struck a deal with international negotiators on the whopping private sector debt only excited the market for some moment. \par \par \uc2  Now, the market is quiet again. Investors seem to be disappointed to see the fact that the rupiah could not go up better than the 10,000 level against the dollar. That position is set to affect many listed companies' performance in the first six months of this year. \par \par \uc2  Such situation has resulted in pressures on blue-chip stocks in the Jakarta Stock Exchange, including forestry and plywood stocks. From June 3 to June 8 the sectoral stocks fell 3.08%. Index fell from 43.91 to 39.47. \par \par \uc2  Barito Pacific Timber fell 27.78%. Its price fell from Rp 450 to Rp 325 over last week with trade volume reaching 28.429 million shares. \par \par \uc2  Sells of Barito shares were seen to reflect investors concern that the company will eventually come under scrutiny due to the fact that the company is closely linked to former president Soeharto family. \par \par \uc2  Amid the height of calls for reformation, shares of companies related to Soeharto family and deemed to contain elements of "corruption, collusion and nepotism," better known as KKN here, become increasingly unpopular. \par \par \uc2  Sumalindo Lestari Jaya shares also fell. It weakened 7.14% last week to Rp 325, with transaction volume reaching 292,000 shares worth Rp 103.862 million. Sumalindo is owned 35.75% by Barito, second after Astra International, 39.92%. \par \par \uc2  In the meantime, Surya Dumai Industri shares registered gain by 2.5%, with its share price moving up slightly to Rp 2,050. \par \par \uc2  Investors believe that product diversification by the company will help increase its export revenues, particularly in view of the US dollar strengthening against the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Overall, interests on forestry and plywood stocks remain fairly stable. Demand for Indonesian logs is on the rise at present. Supply of logs that total more than five million cubic meters, 1.5 million cubic meters above normalcy, shows that the industry is still promising. \par \par \uc2  * Sigma Research Inc. \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du6b001el\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
