\par\par \b \uc2  Rupiah sinks to 14,700 as stocks lose grounds. \b0\par\par\uc2 577 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 June 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The rupiah sank 5 percent yesterday to close at 14,700 against the U.S. dollar as the Japanese yen touched its lowest level since August 1990. \par \par \uc2  The stock market, battered by sinking turnover, slid 0.46 percent despite gains in dollar-valued stocks which were buoyant on the rupiah's fall. \par \par \uc2  Stock analysts said that prevailing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  about domestic political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability were also dragging the market down. \par \par \uc2  "It is so difficult to expect the market to recover in the near future as everyone is in crisis now," Harita Kencana Securities president Christina Lim said. \par \par \uc2  She added the market could well sag further because confidence was absent in a time of crisis and the market still feared that mass rioting could recur at any time in the future. \par \par \uc2  "The market could go down further as there is nothing to look forward to in the near future. People are still scared to invest here. Even today, we heard people were rioting somewhere," she said. \par \par \uc2  It was reported that hundreds of people continued rioting in the town of Tegal in Central Java yesterday, damaging several homes, offices and shops. \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers said the combination of domestic political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and a weak yen hit the rupiah, which was already suffering from market illiquidity. \par \par \uc2  "The yen which fell below 146 to the dollar today (yesterday) was the main culprit behind the fall of the rupiah," a dealer with a local private foreign bank said. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah hit 15,000 yesterday afternoon before closing at 14,700. It had closed at 14,000 on Friday. \par \par \uc2  The dealer added that demand for dollars remained high, especially from local commercial banks as \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  extended the deadline for them to settle outstanding arrears in their interbank and trade finance debt to June 30. \par \par \uc2  "So, we can expect that the rupiah will not recover until June 30 as demand for dollars will remain," he said. \par \par \uc2  He added the sharp fall in the rupiah was aggravated by the very thin trades, with the largest trade amounting to only about one million dollars. \par \par \uc2  In the money market, dealers said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  set rupiah interbank \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  at 51 percent per annum for this week, down from 53 percent last week. \par \par \uc2  "We can expect that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  is actually moving toward lowering \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We should welcome this move. But the problem is that the IMF might not be happy with that kind of move," Manaek Robert Toruan, the head of Bank Niaga's fixed income desk, said. \par \par \uc2  The International Monetary Fund has said that the government should maintain tight money \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to prevent inflation from soaring further. \par \par \uc2  On the stock market, share prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) lost 0.4 percent, with the JSX Composit Index closing 1.871 points lower at 406.501. \par \par \uc2  Total turnover on the JSX was a meager US$18 million yesterday after averaging only $17 million a day last week. \par \par \uc2  Stockbrokers said a heavier fall in the index was prevented by gains in stocks with dollar valuations, like telecommunications stocks Telkom and Indosat and tin miner Tambang Timah, as the rupiah sagged to near 15,000. \par \par \uc2  "If you take Telkom and Indosat out of the market, the market was actually a lot more depressed than you might think," an analyst with a joint venture securities house said. (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du6g006sr\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
