\par\par \b \uc2  Rupiah breaks 15,000 barrier as stocks decline. \b0\par\par\uc2 591 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 June 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The rupiah broke psychologically important level of Rp 15,000 against the U.S. dollar yesterday as local stock prices lost 1.7 percent over persistent domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and a bearish regional market. \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers said the rupiah, which opened at Rp 14,600/700, touched the day low of Rp 15,200 in early trading but recovered slightly in the afternoon to close at Rp 15,100. \par \par \uc2  Yesterday's close was 2 percent down on the previous days value at the end of trading. \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers attributed the fall in the rupiah to a combination of the weakness of the Japanese yen against the dollar, persistent political and social \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and high local demand for the dollar. \par \par \uc2  "We are just hopeless. The market was very thin, the yen remained weak and our political situation is not improving," a dealer with a local private bank said. \par \par \uc2  The Japanese yen slid to over 146 against the American dollar, leaving no scope for the rupiah to reverse its similarly downtrend against the dollar, he said. \par \par \uc2  The dealer added that local commercial banks required a large amount of dollars this month because the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , had extended the deadline for them to settle their dollar debts and trade finance arrears to June 30 from June 12. \par \par \uc2  "I think the rupiah could fall as low as Rp 17,000 over the coming days because certain banks have to settle their dollar obligations," he said. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah touched its lowest ever level of Rp 17,000 against the dollar on Jan. 9. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said worries over political unrest would further hamper recovery of the country's ailing financial market. \par \par \uc2  "Although there were no significant protests today (yesterday), the market senses that the country political situation is far from secure," he said. \par \par \uc2  Hundreds of people rioted in Tegal, Central Java, on Monday, damaging shops, houses and offices. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said intervention in the money market by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , who offered short-term promissory notes (SBIs) at 59 percent - one percent higher than its normal rate of 58 percent - did not improve the rupiah's position against the American dollar. \par \par \uc2  Stock prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) declined 1.7 percent, dragged down by the sharp fall of shares in cross-listed telecommunications firms PT Telkom and PT Indosat, and tin mining firm PT Tambang Timah. \par \par \uc2  The JSX Composite Index fell 6.98 points to 399.51 points yesterday on a total turnover of 190 million shares worth Rp 252 billion (US$16.80 million). \par \par \uc2  Stock prices in Tambang Timah fell Rp 375 to Rp 6,475, Telkom fell Rp 100 to Rp 3,625 and Indosat fell Rp 600 to Rp 14,900. \par \par \uc2  Stockbrokers said the movement of the three stocks would largely determine the direction of the market because of the sheer number of shares traded in these companies. \par \par \uc2  Antonio Yongnata, a dealer with Mashill Jaya Securities, said the absence of offshore funds had worsened the local market. \par \par \uc2  Head of research at Pentasena Securities Mohammad Syahrial said yesterday that daily trading transactions on the local stock market had declined sharply to current levels of around Rp 100 billion, compared to Rp 400 billion several months ago, because most offshore funds had left the country's dire financial market. \par \par \uc2  Another analyst at a local securities house said: "The lack of investor confidence in the local market is the main cause of the bearish stock market." (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du6h006uz\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
