\par\par \b \uc2  Indonesia's  \highlight22\uc2 economy \highlight\uc2  heading for stagnation, says Miranda. \b0\par\par\uc2 569 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 June 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  7 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Current indicators show that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is deteriorating into stagnation which, coupled with current political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , will limit the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  tools available to lift the country out of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  director Miranda Gultom said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  She said that based on statistical convention, an \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  which experiences negative growth for two consecutive quarters was defined to be in a stagnation. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said Indonesia's gross domestic product in this year's first quarter declined more than 6 percent and added "it's clear that there will be negative growth in the second quarter." \par \par \uc2  "The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is like a hollowing tree," she told a seminar. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions in the 1998/1999 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  generated in April are no longer realistic since inflation may surpass 80 percent and the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could contract more than 10 percent, she said. \par \par \uc2  She also argued that the 1998 year-end exchange rate target of Rp 6,000 to the U.S. dollar was no longer realistic. \par \par \uc2  "This problem is further complicated by the country's political developments." \par \par \uc2  She stressed, however, that despite the hurdles, the government had to make best of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  tools in its control to prevent the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  from further deteriorating. \par \par \uc2  Efforts to control inflation and stabilize the rupiah will be increasingly dependent on the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  because the government's expansionary \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  is unavoidable, she said. \par \par \uc2  She pointed out that a larger \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  than previously projected was inevitable due to greater \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  resulting from a further depreciation of the rupiah, while at the same time \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue would likely be less than estimated. \par \par \uc2  "This is why we will maintain a high interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Miranda said. \par \par \uc2  BI's high interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , however, is not supported by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR) which has urged significant reductions in the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's benchmark rate from as high as 58 percent at present. \par \par \uc2  "Reducing the rates would give a wrong signal to the financial market," she said, pointing out that the market expected a tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  amid an expansionary \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  She added that lower \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  would only prompt people to accumulate goods and purchase foreign currency to hedge against increasing inflation and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  She said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , however, would provide more concessional credits to small businesses, which would help revive the production and distribution system for essential goods and provide employment. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is expected to help curb inflation and prevent social unrest, she said. \par \par \uc2  She also said BI would continue injecting liquidity into troubled banks in support of the government's bank guarantee \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to prevent an overall collapse of the country's banking system. \par \par \uc2  She added that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would soon help domestic banks repay their trade financing debts of more than US$1 billion to overseas banks. \par \par \uc2  "This is a condition for the restart of the trade financing facility to the country as agreed to in last month's debt talks in Frankfurt. \par \par \uc2  "All these steps must be carried out consistently, meaning we cannot meet the wishes of all parties at the same time." \par \par \uc2  She said the political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  must also be solved because noneconomic factors were playing a large role in the crisis. \par \par \uc2  "When the party's over, the mess has to be cleaned up."(rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du6i006wp\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
