\par\par \b \uc2  Investors cut operations because of  \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 575 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 June 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  6 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Foreign and local investors have significantly cut the operations of their industrial factories due to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the country's political situation, State Minister of Investment Hamzah Haz said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  "They see the condition still fluctuating and they reduce production activities," Hamzah told reporters on the sidelines of a hearing with \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  Commission V for industry, mining, trade, manpower, the environment and cooperatives. \par \par \uc2  This was evident in the 70 percent decrease in the imports of both foreign and local investors since last year, said Hamzah, who is also the chairman of the Investment Coordinating Board. \par \par \uc2  According to the board, imports of capital goods of both foreign investment and local investment in April were down to US$5.80 million from $113.09 million in the same month last year. \par \par \uc2  In the same month, imports of raw materials also dropped to $150,000, down from $23.88 million in April 1997. \par \par \uc2  "What will happen is a scarcity in manufactured products, as import activities keep declining," Hamzah said. \par \par \uc2  He said local and foreign investors had asked him when the situation would return to normal. \par \par \uc2  "I told them it could take from one to two years," Hamzah said. \par \par \uc2  The government's plan to hold both an extraordinary session of the People's Consultative Assembly and a general election require long and comprehensive preparations, he said \par \par \uc2  "My assumption is that legal preparations for the elections will be finished by March of next year, and will be followed by operational preparations, so that the elections could be conducted at the end of next year at the earliest," he said. \par \par \uc2  But the government must ensure social and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability in order to have safe elections, otherwise more social unrest would occur, he said. \par \par \uc2  There must be adequate supplies of essential goods at affordable prices, and there must be less layoffs, he said. \par \par \uc2  However, Hamzah dismissed speculation that investors had lost interest in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "New applications keep coming, nobody has canceled their investment plans. Our investment activities are not stagnant," he said. \par \par \uc2  Hamzah said investment realization had also declined this year. \par \par \uc2  Between July 1997 and May this year, local investors realized 353 projects with investment worth Rp 19 trillion. In the same period, foreign investors realized 320 projects with investment worth $2.97 billion. \par \par \uc2  He predicted that the realization of investment approvals would continue to decline in the 1998/1999 period. \par \par \uc2  But the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political crisis had set back the country's investment development to equal that of the beginning of 1970s, when the country was working hard to invite foreign investors, he said. \par \par \uc2  The government is currently working on establishing a new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on investment, which includes criteria on eligible recipients of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives. The new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is being finalized and is expected to be completed early next month, he said. \par \par \uc2  The new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will focus on investment activities in the eastern part of the country, he said. \par \par \uc2  It will be set to boost the export sector and to create more job opportunities, as well as support pioneering business fields and agribusiness, capital goods and machinery industries, he said. \par \par \uc2  The new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will also limit the time span of projects' realization to one year, he said. \par \par \uc2  Currently, companies which cannot complete their investment projects within three years can apply for an extension of up to two years, due to the monetary crisis, he said. (das) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du6n003lp\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Manufacturing stocks fluctuate. \b0\par\par\uc2 289 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 June 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA: Manufacturing stocks seemed to be picking up last week but their prices still fluctuated. Investors tended to take on speculative buying for capital gain. \par \par \uc2  The buying move was in tune with the fluctuating macro situation in the Jakarta Stock Exchange. Investors made use of the momentum to buy stocks with capital gain potential. \par \par \uc2  The on-going \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  storm has driven manufacturing companies to the brink of collapse. Adding to the woes are the high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  set by the banking industry. \par \par \uc2  Many manufacturing companies have slashed production due to skyrocketing production cost. In fact, Astra International has stopped production since June 1 due to increasing operational costs. \par \par \uc2  Investors' buying move was therefore technical and temporary in nature, in accord with the macro condition of the Jakarta Stock Exchange and regional bourses. The move also followed the strengthening of shares of big companies and state-owned companies. \par \par \uc2  Tjiwi Kimia strengthened 20% from Rp 1,150 to Rp 1,475. Investors have faith that the increasing prices of paper will boost the company's earning. In general, trading of manufacturing shares proceeded with ample liquidity. \par \par \uc2  Selling action, however, hit other sectors due to negative rumors. Investors put their shares on sale to cut losses. The unstable rupiah value against the US dollar also affected trading in the Jakarta bourse. \par \par \uc2  For investors with penchant for speculation, this appears to be the right time to buy manufacturing shares, whose prices have already nose-dived to a very competitive level, ranging from Rp 150 to Rp 4,000 a share. \par \par \uc2  Investors are still expected, however, to be cautious to individual sentiment. Prices are also very much sensitive to the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  political condition. \par \par \uc2  * Sigma Research Institute, Inc. \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du6o001h7\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
