\par\par \b \uc2  Gloomy outlook expected to overshadow trading. \b0\par\par\uc2 723 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 July 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Trading activities on the country's battered stock market are expected to slow down this week despite positive news on the resumption of international loans to Indonesia, stock analysts and brokers said over the weekend. \par \par \uc2  They said loans from multilateral financial institutions like the World Bank, though positive in nature, would not be able to lift investors confidence in the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  at this point of time. \par \par \uc2  ING Barings Securities' head of research Tom Inglish predicted that trading activities on the local market would be quite sluggish this week after a strong rally last week. \par \par \uc2  "The movement of the Japanese yen will continue to lead the movement of the local market in the short term," he said. \par \par \uc2  An analyst with a local securities house agreed and said domestic factors still had a negative effect on the market as the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis had affected almost all aspects of people's lives. \par \par \uc2  "Indonesia is facing not only an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis but political and social problems as well. It needs a huge move to address all of them," the analyst said. \par \par \uc2  He said the commitment from the World Bank to disburse a US$1 billion structural loan to Indonesia would be far from enough to revive the battered market. \par \par \uc2  "They (multilateral financial institutions) have lost momentum in helping Indonesia because the country is already on the brink of collapse," he said. \par \par \uc2  Reports said the World Bank had approved a $1 billion structural adjustment loan as part of the $43 billion bailout package arranged by the International Monetary Fund (IMF) to help heal the country's dire \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The World Bank and the Group of Seven of industrial countries are expected to announce soon new loans worth $6 billion to supplement the existing package. \par \par \uc2  Head of research of Mashill Jaya Securities Tjandra Kartika said the news would not be strong enough to rally the market. \par \par \uc2  Tjandra said political and social \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  at home, worsened by an increase in the number of poor people and escalating unemployment, would counteract any positive news in the market. \par \par \uc2  He pointed out that unresolved social and political problems would continue to prevent offshore funds from entering here. \par \par \uc2  Bahana Securities' associate director and head of institutional sales, Andre Cita, said political and social stability would be the key factor for trading activities on the local market. \par \par \uc2  "If the situation remains stable and there is no major demonstrations and no much backlash in terms of the situation in Irian Jaya and East Timor, the market will continue to show its strength," he said. \par \par \uc2  Reports said last week that at least one person was killed and two were badly injured in a clash between rioters and security officers in Irian Jaya following a tense situation in East Timor. \par \par \uc2  There were also some sporadic protests staged in several parts of Jakarta last week, demanding that the government root out corruption, nepotism and collusion. \par \par \uc2  Despite all this, Tjandra and Cita said some short-term investors, who had long sidelined the local market, would return to the local exchange to benefit from cheap stocks. \par \par \uc2  Some brokers said that although the country's long-term outlook remain bearish, news of the presence of Mexico's Cemex SA de CV to purchase 35 percent of the government's 65 percent stake in cementmaker PT Semen Gresik would trigger active trading on the local bourse at the beginning of this week. \par \par \uc2  Trading in Semen Gresik stock, which was suspended on Wednesday, will resume today. \par \par \uc2  The Mexican cementmaker offered to buy Semen Gresik shares at $1.38 per share from the government and the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "News on Cemex will prompt investors to make massive buys before Semen Gresik's shares rise higher," a dealer with a local securities house said. \par \par \uc2  The JSX Composite index rose 9 percent to 470.54 points last week from 430.87 the previous week. \par \par \uc2  Daily average turnover was about 340.22 million shares last week compared to 182.97 million the previous week. \par \par \uc2  Daily average transaction value rose to Rp 310.54 billion (US$21.4 million) last week compared to Rp 161.39 billion the previous week. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the rupiah closed at 14,550 to the U.S. dollar last week compared to its close at 14,800 the previous week. (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du77004cm\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
