\par\par \b \uc2  Encouraging news offers only short-lived boost - Analysts. \b0\par\par\uc2 732 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 July 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The government's success in rescheduling most of its debt due this year and in landing multibillion dollar overseas funding are not enough to effect long-lasting confidence in the faltering \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , experts have said. \par \par \uc2  They said yesterday recovery from the year-long \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis remained in the distance, dependent on solving lingering issues such as private debt and banking sector problems, \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the domestic political situation and the market's negative view of the government's populist \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "It's difficult to be optimistic," said head of research at PT SG Securities Indonesia Goei Siaw Hong. \par \par \uc2  He considered the debt rescheduling to be only a temporary remedy for the ailing \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  because debt pressure still existed. \par \par \uc2  "What Indonesia needs is a reduction in the amount of both the sovereign debt and private sector overseas debt." \par \par \uc2  He added that the implementation of a new bankruptcy law would help in reducing pressure from the private sector's overseas debt because a bankrupt entity would no longer be required to pay its debt. \par \par \uc2  But \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the domestic political front created a jittery environment which deterred investors, he said. \par \par \uc2  Markets would pay particular attention to the special session of the People's Consultative Assembly in November, the general election in May and the presidential election in December 1999, he added. \par \par \uc2  Associate director of PT Bahana Securities Andre Cita agreed the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  political situation was a primary contributor to persistent low confidence. \par \par \uc2  "There is still concern on the social and political situation. People are still waiting to see whether there will be more social unrest or rioting." \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita said Monday that foreign lenders had committed to rescheduling about US$1.25 billion in the country's sovereign debt due this year. \par \par \uc2  The agreement is expected to be signed at the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI) donors meeting in Paris at the end of this month. \par \par \uc2  The government has allocated Rp 33.26 trillion ($3.1 billion) for principal payment of its debt during the remaining period of the 1998/1999 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year. \par \par \uc2  The postponement is expected to help the country in financing its huge \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  commitments to help the people survive the country's worst \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis in three decades. \par \par \uc2  The IMF has also announced that several donors including the World Bank, Asian Development, Australia and China had agreed to provide an additional $6 billion on top of the $43 billion IMF-arranged loans to cover the financing gap in the 1998/1999 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which was allowed by the IMF to have a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of 8.5 percent of gross domestic product. \par \par \uc2  The news briefly lifted the rupiah to around Rp 13,000 to the U.S. dollar last Wednesday, but the currency plunged back to more than Rp 14,000 during the following days. The rupiah has lost more than 80 percent in value from its precrisis level of Rp 2,450 in July last year. \par \par \uc2  The additional funding is needed to provide \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  for fuel, basic food items, and a credit program for small businesses. \par \par \uc2  Populist policies \par \par \uc2  "But these are populist policies which will drain our forex \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The market doesn't like this," said Goei. \par \par \uc2  He explained that \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be tolerable at difficult times if they were prioritized to the poor. \par \par \uc2  "It would be a serious problem if President Habibie is trying to satisfy everyone." \par \par \uc2  He also lambasted the government's decision to raise the export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  on crude palm oil. \par \par \uc2  "Why shouldn't we export CPO when we really need more dollars?" He feared the high export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  would only lead to more smuggling of CPO out of the country. \par \par \uc2  Cita said one of the key factors in returning confidence to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was the restoration of the shattered banking sector. \par \par \uc2  "There's still a lot of focus on the banking sector," he said, adding that investors were also waiting to see the implementation of the bankruptcy law. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Justice Muladi said Tuesday that new bankruptcy regulations would be effective by Aug. 22, in which it would only take 30 days to process a bankruptcy case. \par \par \uc2  The IMF's Asia Pacific director Hubert Neiss arrived in Jakarta yesterday on an expected two-week visit to continue reviewing the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du7n004aq\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
