e report, claiming his remarks on looting were taken out of context by the reporter, people would have in mind that the minister should exercise thought in making statements. \par \par \uc2  Regarding press freedom, other controversial issues have been made. The press no longer needs a license to operate but journalists must have a license, which is valid for a limited time. If the journalist is deemed unqualified, his license could be revoked. In implementing this new \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government will, again, have control over the press, creating a 50-year setback for freedom of the press. \par \par \uc2  Our nation needs a people and a government that can work together to overcome this crisis. The people won't support the government if corruption, collusion and nepotism are still practiced. In the Reform Cabinet's first three months of work, not a single minister came out with transparency, only dishonest and silly statements, as Soeharto's regime had in the past. \par \par \uc2  PARLINDUNGAN SIBARANI \par \par \uc2  Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du7u004jc\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
