\par\par \b \uc2  Rupiah strengthens but stocks lose gains. \b0\par\par\uc2 567 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 August 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  9 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The rupiah gained ground yesterday, breaking the 13,000 level against the U.S. dollar in mild dealing, but stock prices fell almost 3 percent due to profit taking on big cap stocks, dealers and stockbrokers said. \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers said the improvement in the Japanese yen to 144.80 against the dollar after a seven-week low Monday helped boost other regional currencies, including the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah, which opened at 13,050 in the early trading session, advanced to touch a day high of 12,800 before closing at 12,900. The currency closed Monday at 13,100. \par \par \uc2  "The rupiah was good today (yesterday), thanks to a stable yen," a chief dealer with a local private bank said. \par \par \uc2  Beside a stable yen, dealers said that intervention by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which sold the dollar in the market through several state-owned banks, also contributed to the strong rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "We saw some state banks sell around US$10 million in the market," the chief dealer said. \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita said in Paris last week the government would use some portion of foreign loans to buy rupiah from the market in an effort to bring the currency to the targeted level of 10,000 to the dollar. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said the rupiah could improve against the dollar in the coming days provided there were no major developments which could worsen the political and security climate. \par \par \uc2  "The rupiah is expected to test the 12,000 point level," the chief dealer said. \par \par \uc2  However, the long-term prospects of the country's financial market remain gloomy because \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the country's political front has not been properly addressed by the government, a dealer said. \par \par \uc2  Despite the strengthening rupiah, stock prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) ended 2.9 percent lower yesterday, spurred by profit taking by investors on large capitalized stocks. \par \par \uc2  The JSX composite price index fell 13.9 points to 461.35 on a total turnover of 152.51 million shares valued at Rp 211.49 billion (US$16.39 million). \par \par \uc2  Losers outnumbered gainers by 68 against 29, with 192 counters unchanged. \par \par \uc2  Stock brokers said the decline in large-cap stocks like state-owned domestic telecommunications firm PT Telkom, state international call operator PT Indosat, state tin miner PT Tambang Timah, state general mining firm PT Aneka Tambang and pulp and paper company PT Tjiwi Kimia helped the benchmark price index fall sharply lower yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Together, the five companies account for about 40 percent of the market capitalization. \par \par \uc2  "Therefore, it is just understandable if their losses have contributed largely to the fall in the main price index," head of research of Mashill Jaya Securities Edhi S. Widjoyo said. \par \par \uc2  The stock price of Telkom fell Rp 225 to Rp 4,125 on 9.81 million shares traded, Indosat shed Rp 525 to Rp 13,825 on 221,000 shares, Tambang Timah slid Rp 200 to Rp 8,300 on 181,000 shares, Tjiwi Kimia dropped Rp 350 to Rp 2,600 on 2.57 million shares and Aneka Tambang dropped Rp 50 to Rp 2,400 on 9.08 million shares. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, cigarette maker PT HM Sampoerna gained Rp 75 to Rp 3,250 on 5.29 million shares, and competitor PT Gudang Garam was unchanged at Rp 8,800. (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du85004q5\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pich