\par\par \b \uc2  Jakarta market plunges over bearish sentiment. \b0\par\par\uc2 616 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 August 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  9 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Rupiah started the week weaker yesterday in line with the falling yen and the bearish domestic sentiment, and the local bourse followed suit. \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers said the trading volume of the rupiah-dollar was thin, which they attributed to Singapore's closure due to its national day holiday. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah closed at 12,950/13,050 against the dollar on the Jakarta spot market, weaker than its Friday close of 12,750. \par \par \uc2  "The rupiah weakened as the Japanese yen also weakened. It's always that way," a dealer with a local private bank said. \par \par \uc2  The yen broke the 146 level to the dollar in Asian trading. Dealers said the weak yen sent ripples through the rest of the region. \par \par \uc2  In addition, dealers said the domestic situation was not improving, either on political or \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fronts. The market remains worried that more social unrest may occur ahead of the country's independence day on Aug. 17. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which was spotted intervening in the market late last week, did not make its presence felt yesterday. \par \par \uc2  State banks did offer the dollar at the 13,000 level, albeit in a very small amount, they said. \par \par \uc2  "If the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  or state banks intervene when the market size is very thin like now, it would help the rupiah a lot," the dealer said. \par \par \uc2  He noted that slight intervention by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  through state banks last week had helped the rupiah strengthen to 12,700. \par \par \uc2  Share prices \par \par \uc2  The weaker rupiah coupled with an \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  domestic political situation caused share prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) to close sharply lower for the ninth consecutive day yesterday. \par \par \uc2  The JSX composite index closed down 2.446 points at 421.167. Volume stood at a meager 150.22 million shares valued at Rp 153.46 billion. \par \par \uc2  Losers outnumbered gainers 85 to 29, with 85 stocks unchanged and 90 others untraded. \par \par \uc2  Trimegah Securindo Lestari's research head David Chang said many local investors who had dominated trading for some time lodged selling orders due to concerns over possible riots before Aug. 17. \par \par \uc2  "Many local investors are quite worried about the rumors going around about social unrest," Chang said. \par \par \uc2  "Today is worse because people spread unfounded rumors that Gen. Wiranto (the Armed Forces commander) was shot. I myself don't believe it, but many people thought it was true." \par \par \uc2  In addition, Chang said, some investors were switching their investments in the equities market into the riskless \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  promissory notes (SBI) offering high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  offers a one-month SBI rate at 58 percent per annum. But one-month SBIs sold through auction last week offered an average rate of 68.33 percent per annum. \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 Interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  have increased again. This is bad for the stock market," Chang said. \par \par \uc2  Most large-cap stocks were down yesterday, except heavyweight state-owned telecommunications firm PT Telkom which gained Rp 125 to close at Rp 3,725 on 1.1 million shares traded. \par \par \uc2  International telephone service operator PT Indosat fell Rp 225 to Rp 10,875 on 341,500 shares traded. Cigarettemaker PT HM Sampoerna lost Rp 200 to Rp 2,800 on 4.2 million shares, and competitor PT Gudang Garam slid Rp 125 to Ro 7,875 on 1.1 million shares. \par \par \uc2  The market yesterday saw the trading suspension of multifinance firm PT Putra Surya Multidana as its stock prices touched bottom at Rp 25 per share. \par \par \uc2  Dealers and analysts see the market outlook for the rest of the week to stay bearish due to the potential downward pressure from the domestic political situation. (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du8b004z8\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
