\par\par \b \uc2  Economists urge govt to liberalize CPO trading. \b0\par\par\uc2 482 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 August 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Economists have again urged the government to liberalize trade in crude palm oil (CPO) and cooking oil to boost the country's foreign exchange earnings. \par \par \uc2  Bungaran Saragih, an economist at Bogor Institute of Agriculture, said yesterday the government would earn at least US$2 billion from CPO exports in this financial year if it liberalized the trade. \par \par \uc2  "The government should promote the export of commodities which have the potential to be large foreign exchange earners to help the country out of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. The CPO industry falls into that category and any increase in exports would also be of benefit to smallholder farmers," Bungaran said in a discussion on oil palm plantation management and the CPO and cooking oil industries. \par \par \uc2  Bungaran said government intervention to stabilize cooking oil prices had not only been ineffective but had also caused trading in the commodity to become a very \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  business. \par \par \uc2  "Inconsistency in government regulations covering trade in CPO and cooking oil will kill the business in the long term because the international market will come to view involvement with Indonesian palm oil producers as fraught with risk and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  Nawir Messi from the Institute for Development Economics and Finance (INDEF) said the government \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of imposing a high \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the export of CPO had cost the country $384 million in lost revenue this year. \par \par \uc2  Speaking at the same discussion, Nawir said the export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  had cost the CPO processing industry $99 million and oil palm plantation owners $400 million in lost revenue, $200 million of which would have found its way to smallholder oil palm farmers. \par \par \uc2  In contrast, the increase in the export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  from 40 percent to 60 percent would earn the government a mere $126 million per annum in extra revenue. \par \par \uc2  He argued that funding for the government \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to maintain a reference price for cooking oil would increase to about $123 million this year as a result of the increase in the export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The government plans to use the funds raised through the export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  to subsidize cooking oil prices on the domestic market. \par \par \uc2  Nawir said it was the middle and upper classes of society that were reaping the benefits of the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , not the poor at whom it was supposed to be targeted. \par \par \uc2  "The high export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  has adversely affected the welfare of smallholder oil palm farmers and helped those who are already rich," he said. \par \par \uc2  Both Bungaran and Nawir shared the view that if the government really wanted to help the poor then it should abolish the price \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on cooking oil and instead use the money to provide the needy with an income \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The two economists said the money would be better spent in a program designed specifically to improve the welfare of the country's poor. (gis) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du8l004zu\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
